node.text:
Freshly out of oven! Anyhow score, anyhow shape, anyhow bake! Didn’t proof in rattan banneton basket nor bake in cast iron pot. Just proof in my mixing bowls and put on baking tray to bake in oven. That’s my humble sourdoughs that my family loves eating! 😋 .

Looks like one from the bakery!

@qwkay I don’t intend to get as got too many baking stuffs at home. Actually if you don’t mind the look, can just put in metal mixing bowl laid with baking paper to proof. I transferred the proofed bread onto baking tray and bake on the lowest rack using the highest temp 250°C with steam intensity 3 (my Bosch oven is a steam combi one which can release steam during baking) if you don’t have steam function, can put a tray of ice at the bottom to create steam during baking.

@qwkay the texture is not compromise, tastes good! You can scroll back to my posts around June/July last year when I first started baking sourdough and adventurous to try in different natural flavors. Take a look as those posts have photos showing the proofed dough as well as in the oven baking photos for reference. 😊
